note.value: This ontology addresses gaps in existing CIDOC-CRM extensions (CRMba, CRMsoc) by modeling Nepal-specific institutional forms (Guthi), ritual activation of sacred space, and multi-source provenance reconciliation.

Competency Questions: (1) Which rituals activate which deities at which sites? (2) How do Guthis mediate temple-ritual-community relationships? (3) What is the provenance chain for contested construction dates? (4) How do syncretic deities bridge Hindu-Buddhist practices spatially and temporally?

definition.value: An event-centric LinkML schema for Nepal cultural heritage, fully aligned with CIDOC-CRM and PROV-O, enabling assertion-level provenance tracking and ritual-spatial-temporal reasoning.
